      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Good contest to start the day. LOERA (7) three-year-old Capitalist filly from Golden Slipper winner Overreach on debut for the Waterhouse & Bott yard. Has impressed in her two latest trial wins in good time. Hard to run down. ALPHA ZETA (4) covered ground early at debut and never surrendered with a game third over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Maps well from the inside gate and not without top-three claims in this tougher race. COMPENSATION (1) chased hard on debut as the $1.75 fav with a handy third over 1100m at Warwick Farm. Likely to push forward and will benefit greatly with that run under the belt. MRS MAREE (3) resumes from a lengthy break. Not far away when second in a Super Maiden over 1200m at Warwick Farm last September. Fitted with the two trial wins and Rawiller rides from an inside gate. Keep safe.",
